wikipedia_page.main: Henry Bailey (2 December 1897 – 1965), sometimes known as Harry Bailey, was an English professional footballer who made over 140 appearances as a goalkeeper in the Football League for Exeter City. He also played league football for Luton Town, Brentford and Thames.
